        "title": "fix(ollama): yield during dense stream processing",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- ports the Ollama dense stream cooperative-yield fix from https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/86633 onto a current maintainer branch, preserving @udaymanish6 as commit author\n- yields and checks aborts while draining dense native Ollama NDJSON chunks so one large read cannot monopolize the Gateway event loop\n- adds a regression test that proves timers can run before dense stream processing completes\n\nRefs https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/86599.\nSupersedes https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/86633 as the rebased maintainer branch.\n\n## Verification\n\nBehavior addressed: dense native Ollama stream chunks now cooperatively yield during parsing instead of draining an entire large read in one synchronous loop.\n\nReal environment tested: AWS Crabbox Linux changed gate on the maintained branch before the latest clean rebase, focused local Vitest wrapper in a Codex worktree after the latest rebase, formatter/lint/diff checks, and branch autoreview.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```sh\ngit diff --check origin/main...HEAD\nnode_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/ollama/src/stream.ts extensions/ollama/src/stream.test.ts\nnode_modules/.bin/oxlint extensions/ollama/src/stream.ts extensions/ollama/src/stream.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/ollama/src/stream.test.ts --reporter=dot\n.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main\nnode scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider aws --idle-timeout 45m --ttl 90m --timing-json --shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"\n```\n\nEvidence after fix: focused local wrapper passed `extensions/ollama/src/stream.test.ts` with 11/11 tests after rebasing to `97ab3fd0d60`; oxfmt, oxlint, and diff checks passed; autoreview reported no accepted/actionable findings with `overall: patch is correct (0.78)`. Earlier AWS Crabbox `check:changed` passed with provider `aws`, lease `cbx_44ae10129cdd`, slug `golden-prawn`, run `run_565207623b61`, machine `c7a.8xlarge`, exit 0, `leaseStopped=true`, lanes `extensions` and `extensionTests`.\n\nObserved result after fix: dense stream unit coverage confirms timer progress during parser drain, and changed extension type/lint/import-cycle guards passed remotely.\n\nWhat was not tested: Windows local-daemon reproduction from https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/86599 was not rerun in this PR. The AWS Crabbox changed gate was not rerun after the latest clean rebase because the patch stayed scoped to the same two Ollama files; this is one mitigation in the broader event-loop starvation cluster, not the final issue closeout by itself.\n",
